Citizen Chen Qin hasn't been downstairs for over 20 days. Without food or daily necessities, she would send them to the property staff via the community Wechat Group, and the community or property would buy them and send them to her door. "I wasn't used to it at first, but I'm used to it now. "

As of 2400 hours on February 17,2020,250 new cases of pneumonia had been reported in Enshi Tujia and Miao Autonomous Prefecture, Hubei. This figure, just higher than the Shennongjia, Qianjiang, located in the "hard-hit areas" of Hubei Ensch, is very rare.

Enshi Tujia and Miao Autonomous Prefecture lies in the southwest of Hubei Province, where Hubei, Hunan and Chongqing provinces meet. It is the only autonomous prefecture in Hubei Province. Wuhan is more than 500 kilometers away from here, the total population of the state of more than 400 million people, the area under the jurisdiction of rural, mountain more.

In Enshi Tujia and Miao Autonomous Prefecture, 853,900 people worked outside the home in the first half of 2019, according to the Enshi Tujia and Miao Autonomous Prefecture Bureau of Statistics. During the Spring Festival, a large number of people go home, to the epidemic prevention and control brought great pressure. In Longtanping, a mountain village in Enshi Tujia and Miao Autonomous Prefecture, there are 11 groups of 1,117 villagers, of whom 199 are returnees.

On February 6, the day after the outbreak, Enshi Tujia and Miao Autonomous Prefecture held a new epidemic prevention and control work, emphasizing the implementation of the strictest traffic control; implementation of the Strictest Prevention and control measures; implementation of the Strictest Control Requirements; implementation of the strictest control disciplines. The outside world calls it "the four strictest" .

Now, Ensch has largely concluded its first round of mapping of returnees, people with fever, confirmed cases and close contacts with suspected cases. At present, the epidemic prevention work in the whole prefecture has entered a state of normality: All villages (communities) are under close management and are guarded by special people. Villagers are not allowed to go out unless there are special circumstances.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Members of the "sharp knife squad" stand guard at the entrance of Yingkou Village, Wangying town, Enshi City, Hubei Province. Photo courtesy of the respondents



No one shall return to the state without special needs during the period of prevention and control

February 13, the property manager of the harmonious home district, Chen Minzhi, is in the office of the returnees, a routine call-back visit. Chen Minzhi told the Beijing News reporter, harmonious home is a comprehensive community, low-rent housing, public rental housing, affordable housing, a total of 22, a total of 2820 households. The structure of community personnel is complex, the flow is frequent, the work is difficult, the task is heavy.

In order to complete the mapping work as soon as possible, she and her colleagues kept calling each household to inquire about the situation. If you can't get in touch with a tenant, you have to come to the house. Some of the residents don't understand. She's been slammed. "shouting at the door for more than 10 minutes, residents do not answer a lot of cases. "

Li Zerong, a member of the Huangniba Community Neighborhood Committee in Enshi City, visited 412 households and about 1,200 people. In order to finish the work as soon as possible, Li Zerong and his colleagues work overtime until more than 10 pm every day.

On February 6, Enshi Tujia and Miao Autonomous Prefecture required that all people entering the state, close contacts of confirmed and suspected cases, and people with fever be checked and accounted for in a timely manner, and strictly implement the provisions of Home Observation, isolation, medical treatment and other measures. At the same time, the out-of-state staff, during the prevention and control period no special need to return to the state.

Li Xianhua is a community volunteer, February 1, he will be in the area at the gate on duty, screening. On February 7, he received a call from a community member who told him that a relative of the resident wanted to return to Ensch from Hunan.

"It's more dangerous for people to move around, and now it's safest to separate them, " Li said, repeatedly urging residents to dissuade relatives from returning for the time being. Eventually, he persuaded relatives to abandon plans to return to Ensch.

A reporter from the HSINKING newspaper learned that at present, all the residential areas in Ensch are under closed management. Every three days, one resident can send one person to purchase daily necessities. Residential property will be in and out of the registration, temperature measurement and return visit.

"We ask residents not to go out without special circumstances. We do all the work for them when they need to go out, " Li told the Beijing News, at present, the city in addition to supermarkets and pharmacies are still in normal operation, other shops have been suspended. "Our daily life is a two-way street between the neighborhood and the supermarket. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Fruit picked by volunteers for residents

"running team" buys living materials for villagers

Songshuping village "sharp knife class" , by the village cadres, cadres and volunteers in the village. Wang Qiang, a member of the knife squad, told the Beijing News that in early February, he began going door to door to find out what was going on with the villagers. At work, he found a villager who had been in close contact with a newly diagnosed case of pneumonia. After persuasion, the villager agreed to stay in isolation for 14 days.

During the isolation period, the village committee arranged for a staff member and a village doctor to visit the family every day to take their temperature and have their bodies examined. Wang Qiang also visited the villagers'homes to ask questions and help him buy daily necessities.

In order to control the epidemic, villagers in villages and towns in Ensch are strictly prohibited from leaving the villages, people without connections are prohibited from entering the villages, vehicles are prohibited from passing through the villages, and special people are on duty at the entrance of the villages round the clock. Among them, Dongxiacao village from the afternoon of January 25, the village closed, 9 intersections are blocked by vehicles, debris, the only one left a channel, set up a barrier, 24 hours someone on duty.

"No chicken from outside the village is allowed to come in, " said Li Xin, a villager. Cars are not allowed to enter the village, and no one from outside the village is allowed to go in. Only those with fever or serious illness are allowed to go out.

Strict control at the same time, the village community set up a "running team" for the people on behalf of the purchase of living materials, in order to prevent the spread of the epidemic caused by the movement of people.

Village Cadre Zhang Quan and colleague often drive a Gold Cup car, go to the supermarket in the town to buy daily necessities, three times a week. The whole village needs the goods, by them to purchase, and then according to the "order" delivery to the villagers at the door. "The thing is put in the doorway, send wechat notice next, person and person do not meet at all. " Zhang Quan tells Beijing News reporter.

In addition, in order to deal with the epidemic situation, January 28, by the idle guesthouse transformation of Enshi City military recruitment Chinese Medicine Observation Point, officially put into use.

There are a total of 30 medical staff, a total of 92 rooms, to accommodate 78 suspected cases of new coronary pneumonia. A number of hotels and community health service centres have also been transformed into separate areas for close contacts and confirmed cases. In addition, the township health center synchronous construction of centralized isolation points, the establishment of fever clinics to do "outpost. ".

Qin Haiyan, a physician at the Longfeng Township Health Center, told the Beijing News that her department had been designated as a fever clinic, operating on two 24-hour shifts. Her job is primarily to screen patients for fever. Those with a history of fever in Wuhan should have blood taken and chest x-rays taken. After a discussion by a group of experts, they should be admitted for observation or transferred to a downtown hospital.

On February 1, when Qin Haiyan was on duty, two patients in the department suddenly developed fever and cough. After a comprehensive diagnosis, she determined that the two were highly suspicious patients. After she reported the information, the hospital quickly conducted an expert consultation, and then sent a doctor to accompany the patient to the downtown hospital.

At the end of each shift, she would pull down her protective suit, exhausted, and fall asleep sitting down. "I've never experienced such a huge workload before. Each patient needs to be seen individually, and after the diagnosis, we need to sterilize it completely before we can diagnose the next patient. " She was afraid to video-chat with her family to avoid family worries. "I'm a bit haggard, so I'll leave the beauty to my family. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The villagers of Xiagou village blocked the entrance to the village with lorries. Photo courtesy of the respondents

Vehicles without access cards and special mission registration are advised to return on site

Since February 2, New Enshi City pneumonia control and Prevention Headquarters issued a traffic control notice, from February 2 at 12:00, the closure of four highways in the area of entrances and exits and green passages.

On February 10, police officer Wu Lichang was transferred to the high-speed inspection bayonet support. He and a number of civilian police shift, 24-hour duty check in the gap. Wu Lichang said that vehicles without a pass and special mission registration are not allowed to enter and are advised to return on the spot.

At first, some people do not understand, do not cooperate, Wu Lichang can only give them reason again and again, "the rules should be strictly implemented, no matter what reason, need to comply, this is for the good of everyone. "

For Vehicles Allowed to enter, Wu Lichang will check the body temperature of all personnel inside the vehicle and make a detailed registration. "Identification Information, where he came from, what he does, all need to be registered, " he said, adding that he would leave contact details of people who had entered and report them to the relevant authorities for follow-up.

Disinfection is also the focus of epidemic prevention and control. A volunteer from honghualing village, Guandu Kou town, Badong County, Zhou Anhong, regularly disinfects and disinfects the village. Each time, he wore a mask, gloves, carrying a red plastic bucket, filled with five liters of disinfectant, in the village of centralized settlements, open-air sports facilities, densely populated areas, home before and after the house, garbage kiosks and other places for disinfection and sterilization.

In order to assist the relevant departments to carry out the work of disinfection of key parts, the Enshi City People's Armed Forces Department mobilized its own militia, set up epidemic prevention and disinfection militia sub-units to carry out the disinfection of key parts. Every morning at 8 am, Li Ze and his teammates will put on protective equipment and carry on their backs two "spray guns" to carry out carpet-style, no-dead-corner epidemic prevention and disinfection in densely populated areas of the market town.

They work from 8 a.m. to 12 noon, traveling through the city's main office halls, neighborhoods, train stations, farmers'markets and other important areas. The team used water jets to wash the ground, and sprayers for areas not reached by the water jets. "Now, you can walk 10,000 steps in a morning, " Li Ze said.

Most strict prevention and control discipline: 84 people held accountable by discipline inspection and supervision organs

Under the outbreak, Enshi Tujia and Miao Autonomous Prefecture has adopted "the strictest control and discipline" . The state requires greater accountability. For those who do not do what they are ordered to do, those who are forbidden to do it, those who work in a dishonest manner, those who have a floating style, those who are greedy for life and are afraid of death, those who shirk their responsibilities, those who act in a disorderly manner, those who do not act, those who do not act, and those who do not act slowly, they should strike with lightning and enforce discipline with an iron hand, strict accountability, for causing serious consequences and adverse impact, the first on-site dismissal and then investigate and deal with."

The Hsinking news learned that the Enshi Tujia and Miao Autonomous Prefecture Commission for Discipline Inspection and supervision had previously publicly reported four typical cases of violations of discipline in the prevention and control of the epidemic, ten cadres have been held accountable for "cutting open and cutting the head off the snake" in rural areas over problems such as inadequate prevention and control of the epidemic and formalism bureaucracy.

Enshi Tujia and Miao Autonomous Prefecture's discipline inspection and supervision authorities have also opened a 24-hour reporting hotline to facilitate supervision channels and accept complaints and reports at any time. Up to now, the discipline inspection and supervision organs investigated and dealt with 46 problems, and held 84 people accountable.

After the outbreak of the epidemic, more than 2,400 village (community) information inspectors from all over the state went to every village to participate in the work of personnel screening, Traffic Control and epidemic prevention knowledge dissemination, and promptly supervise the prevention and control work at the grass-roots level, as well as the formalism, bureaucracy.

Chang Hao is an information monitor in the village. During the epidemic prevention, his main work in the checkpoint on duty and publicity of epidemic prevention and control knowledge. In addition, Chang Hao often travels around the village to see if preventive measures are in place and to ask villagers for advice on preventive measures. "Our job is to find problems and report them. "
